174th Street, east side, north of Sixty-seventh Ave., showing two homes. The brown house faces Fresh Meadow Road. According to Eugene L. Armbruster who received his information from Cornelius Lawrence, the owners (or occupants) were: one Hoagland; J. West, 1860; and D. West, 1873-1891. This place seen in the two views was demolished in May 1934.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
